<div class="info-panel">
  <div class="info-card production">
    <h3>Production Hubs</h3>
    <div class="stat">~80% from Syria</div>
    <p>Under the Assad regime, Syria produced the vast majority of global Captagon. Key zones: Latakia (port), Damascus suburbs, Daraa. Lebanon's Bekaa Valley served as a secondary hub. Post-Dec 2024: 15 industrial labs and 13 storage facilities dismantled.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="info-card transit">
    <h3>Transit Countries</h3>
    <div class="stat">Jordan · Iraq · Turkey</div>
    <p>Jordan is the primary overland corridor (69M+ tablets seized in 2022). Iraq's Al Anbar province is an expanding chokepoint. Turkey serves as a land bridge to European markets. Methods include drones, tunnels, and armored vehicles.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="info-card destination">
    <h3>Primary Destinations</h3>
    <div class="stat">Saudi Arabia #1</div>
    <p>Saudi Arabia accounts for ~67% of all global Captagon seizures (2012–2021). Other markets: UAE, Kuwait, Qatar, Bahrain, Oman. Since Dec 2024, 177M+ tablets intercepted across the Arab region.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="info-card emerging">
    <h3>Emerging Zones (Post-2024)</h3>
    <div class="stat">Yemen · Europe · N. Africa</div>
    <p>Post-Assad decentralization: Houthi-controlled labs discovered in Yemen (2025). Western/Central Europe and North Africa used as diversion and repackaging points. Trade shifting from state monopoly to non-state actors.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="sources">
  <strong>Sources:</strong> UNODC World Drug Report 2025; UNODC Research Brief (Dec 2025); New Lines Institute Comprehensive Captagon Trade Database; Carnegie Endowment for International Peace; Combating Terrorism Center at West Point (Oct 2025). Map is schematic and illustrative of major reported trafficking flows.
</div>

<div class="tooltip" id="tooltip"></div>

<script>
const tooltip = document.getElementById('tooltip');
document.querySelectorAll('[data-tip]').forEach(el => {
  el.style.cursor = 'pointer';
  el.addEventListener('mouseenter', e => {
    const [title, ...rest] = el.getAttribute('data-tip').split('|');
    tooltip.innerHTML = '<div class="tt-title">' + title + '</div>' + rest.join('|');
    tooltip.classList.add('visible');
  });
  el.addEventListener('mousemove', e => {
    let x = e.clientX + 14, y = e.clientY + 14;
    if (x + 240 > window.innerWidth) x = e.clientX - 240;
    if (y + 100 > window.innerHeight) y = e.clientY - 110;
    tooltip.style.left = x + 'px';
    tooltip.style.top = y + 'px';
  });
  el.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => tooltip.classList.remove('visible'));
});
</script>
